"when" makes the node conditional, i.e. if the expression evaluates to "false", the node cannot be present.  But all keys must always be present, which is why "when" is not allowed on key leafs.

You need to use a "must" expression in the list node to do what you're looking for, for example:

    list foo {
      ...
      must "a or b or c";
     leaf a { ... }
     leaf b { ... }
     leaf c { ... }
   }

