Hey, 

Actually I do use a similar directive

```Javascript
.directive('crmSelectAll', function () {
      return {
        restrict: 'E',
        template: '<input type="checkbox" ng-model="isAllSelected" />',
        scope: {
          all: '='
        },
        link: function (scope, element, attr) {

          scope.$watch('isAllSelected', function () {
            if (scope.all) {
              scope.all.forEach(function (val) {
                val.isSelected = scope.isAllSelected;
              })
            }
          });

          scope.$watch('all', function (newVal, oldVal) {
            if (oldVal) {
              oldVal.forEach(function (val) {
                val.isSelected = false;
              });
            }

            scope.isAllSelected = false;
          });
        }
      }
    });
```

There is no particular plan to add such thing into core module. I am not sure you would need smart table for that as anyway smart table already "pollute" the model by adding the isSelected property. I believe it is relevant however when we are in single mode selection as there is a bit of logic to check and a state to keep

@lorenzofox3 Hi, I noticed this pull request was mentioned in the changelog for v2.1.4, but the code doesn't seem to be present in the release. Was it not included for some reason?

I ran into the same issue just now as Matthew described, we're using a model inside service and publishing that in controller, then updating it with angular.copy(). This causes Smart-Table to not detect the updates if the length of the backing array doesn't change.

I did manage to work around by updating the safeCopy from outside with a directive, but that seems fairly brittle (relying on internals of Smart-Table), so would be nice to have this included.

