Regarding the complexity: it's `O(n log n)` (because of the sort), which is linear for all practical purposes in the real world. A naive pairwise search would be `O(n^2)`, so I avoided that. If you feel `O(n log n)` is too big, lemme know and I'll try to bring it down to linear (although I should note that asymptotic complexity is often misleading; the constants are hidden and a linear solution might be much slower than a log-linear solution).

