@ZeLarpMaster  Tagging you on this as in interested party to a path towards a potential resolution:

```py
leading_block_re = re.compile(r"^(`{3}(py)?)(?=\s)")
def cleanup_code(code):
    if code.startswith('`' * 3) and code.endswith('`' * 3):
        code = leading_block_re.sub("", code)[:-3]
    return code.strip()
```
(I've constructed this to display properly in the discord webhook, but the actual source code should just use the triple backticks)

This should work for every case other than the very first thing someone putting in a code block being `py` intended as part of the code, which seems like such an edge case that we should put a note in the doc-string and be done with it.

